Software Engineer, Xerox Singapore Software Center, Singapore. Oct 1998 - Jun 1999 Show details
Unix Printer Driver - The company was developing a GUI print/fax driver UNIX (particularly for SunOS/Solaris, AIX, HP-UX and Linux). The software parses PostScript files (generated from an arbitrary source), displays a GUI showing the options for the target printer, modifies the PostScript files according to the user selections, and finally submits the file to the printer. While seemingly easy, the implementation was made difficult because: (1) the software must produce a different GUI based on the specifications read from a so-called PPD file (a standard file format for specifying a printer's capabilities), (2) the same source must compile for all target platforms, (3) the library used was X/Xt/Motif. (Note that this project was prior to the general availability of CUPS.) The team consisted of 4 programmers.

Research Assistant, Nuclear Microscopy Lab, Department of Physics, National University of Singapore, Singapore. Jul 1995 - Feb 1997 Show details
Pollution surveillance through micro-PIXE - We used an MLEM (Maximum Likelihood Expectation Maximization)-based method on radiation data collected using the nuclear method known as micro-PIXE (micro Particle Induced X-ray Emission), upon aerosol and sediment samples we collected from various locations in Singapore. The method reconstructed the in vivo structures of these samples (similar to PET scans in hospitals), and allowed us to determine their physical compositions accurately. These information were then used by the Ministry of Environment to evaluate the pollution levels of Singapore.

Selected Publications

Calibur: An efficient tool for clustering large numbers of protein decoys (Docs)
S. C. Li and Y. K. Ng (co-first author), BMC Bioinformatics. 11:25, 2010.
The resultant C++ clustering tool Calibur (External) has been incorporated into RosettaCommons (External), a software suite for protein modeling. (Calibur is the preferred clustering application (External) in RosettaCommons.)

On protein structure alignment under distance constraint (Docs)
S. C. Li and Y. K. Ng (co-first author), Theoretical Computer Science 412(32): 4187-4199, 2011.

Finding all longest common segments in protein structures efficiently (Docs)
Y. K. Ng, L. Yin, H. Ono, S. C. Li, IEEE/ACM Transactions on Computational Biology and Bioinformatics. 12(3):644-655, 2015. The resultant 3D segment extraction tool, alcs (External), written in C++, is available under an open source license.

NGS-based likelihood ratio for identifying contributors in two- and three-person DNA mixtures (Docs)
J. M. W. Chan, Z. Zhao, S. C. Li, Y. K. Ng (corresponding author), Computational Biology and Chemistry 74: 428-433, 2018.
